                 <lb/>
                  <quote type="biblical" ana="Heb 6.17">the <normalised orig="stablenesse" auto="false">stableness</normalised> of his<lb/>
<normalised orig="counsell" auto="true">counsel</normalised>, bound <normalised orig="himselfe" auto="true">himself</normalised> by an oath</quote>,<lb/>
                  <quote type="biblical" ana="Heb 6.18"><normalised orig="wherin" auto="true">wherein</normalised> it is impossible that God should<lb/>
lie; that we might <normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised> strong <normalised orig="consolatio~" auto="false">consolation</normalised></quote>.<lb/>
As the <normalised orig="lawes" auto="true">laws</normalised> of the Medes &amp; Persians<lb/>
were <normalised orig="vnrepealable" auto="false">unrepealable</normalised>: so is the decree<lb/>
of almighty God concerning death <normalised orig="vnrepealable" auto="false">unrepealable</normalised>,<lb/>
and in regard of the <normalised orig="euerlastingnes" auto="false">everlastingness</normalised><lb/>
of it, <normalised orig="Ieremy" auto="true">Jeremy</normalised> said, It <quote type="biblical" ana="Jer 17.1">is written<lb/>
