so <normalised orig="sinne" auto="true">sin</normalised> by the law <normalised orig="doth" auto="true">does</normalised> alienate &amp;<lb/>
put away the <normalised orig="soule" auto="true">soul</normalised> from the body of <normalised orig="euerie" auto="true">every</normalised><lb/>
man. Elihu <normalised orig="spake" auto="true">spoke</normalised> must <normalised orig="diuinely" auto="true">divinely</normalised> to<lb/>
this purpose, with his friends: God will<lb/>
render <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> man according to his work<lb/>
and <quote type="biblical" ana="Job 34.11">cause <normalised orig="euery" auto="true">every</normalised> man to find according<lb/>
to his way.</quote> And as <normalised orig="sinne" auto="true">sin</normalised> increased from<lb/>
age to age, so did the anger of God, as<lb/>
